description: Redid the guitar instrumentation. Now you have a clean electric, nylon acoustic, and steel acoustic track. I also added in some notes on how you can accomplish this live without extra guitarists. Only 2 guitar/bass tracks are ever playing at the same time, so if your bassist can use an extra onstage guitar or a 6 string guitar equipped with a GK3 for their bass tones (which would be ideal, since you'd want synth bass tones for this song) they can use the GK3 or a piezo pickup for acoustic tones and play the chorus parts. The nylon parts can be played by the guitarist by switching to a piezo pickup. Which of the two plays the acoustic and the nylon parts can also be switched, if you'd rather have the bassist cover the nylon parts and the guitarist the steel acoustic parts.
